									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Hi, my question is. Once the cacao butter is removed which is virtually half the content of the nib and also being mono and saturated fats, can the raw cacao powder left still maintain the important nutrients and benefits of serotonin and dopamine, vitamins etc or do the butter fats give these benifits. I am wanting to use the raw cacao powder without the fats but im scared of losing nutritional benefits. Basically, will I be taking a substandard cacao without its butter(fats ) content? I have researched so much but cannot get a definitive answer. Hope you can help. Oh and where is the theobromine? In butter or powder left once seperated? Your article was the most informative that I have read. Wonderful.</p>
